%20the%20GOP%20has%20struggled%20with%20suburban%20and%20college-educated%20voters%2C%20an%20issue%20the%20party%20must%20address.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20decades%20past%2C%20an%20array%20of%20US%20counties%20that%20contain%20some%20of%20the%20country's%20most%20prominent%20college%20towns%20were%20often%20closely%20split%20between%20Democrats%20and%20Republicans%2C%20reflective%20of%20the%20more%20liberal-oriented%20university%20centers%20and%20more%20moderate-to-conservative%20suburbs%20and%20exurbs%20balancing%20each%20other%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20many%20of%20these%20towns%20and%20cities%20have%20grown%20in%20population%2C%20combined%20with%20the%20Democratic%20Party's%20dominance%20among%20college-educated%20voters%20and%20those%20with%20advanced%20degrees%2C%20many%20of%20these%20counties%20have%20begun%20to%20rack%20up%20huge%20margins%20for%20Democratic%20candidates%20up%20and%20down%20the%20ballot.%20These%20wins%20are%20poised%20to%20threaten%20GOP%20competitiveness%20in%20key%20states%20like%20Georgia%20and%20Wisconsin%20in%202024%20and%20beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Georgia%20has%20trended%20Republican%20for%20decades%20on%20the%20statewide%20level%2C%20the%20growing%20liberal%20strength%20in%20Athens%20%E2%80%94%20home%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Georgia%20%E2%80%94%20has%20boosted%20Democratic%20margins%20in%20Clarke%20County%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202000%2C%20then-Vice%20President%20Al%20Gore%20beat%20then-Texas%20Gov.%20George%20W.%20Bush%20in%20Athens-Clarke%20County%2052.5%25-41%25%2C%20a%20solid%20victory%20for%20a%20Democratic%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20years%20went%20on%2C%20the%20margins%20moved%20dramatically%20in%20the%20Democratic%20direction%20as%20the%20party's%20presidential%20nominees%20won%20increasingly%20larger%20shares%20of%20the%20vote%20in%20Athens-Clarke%20County%2C%20even%20as%20Georgia%20remained%20a%20GOP-leaning%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20Peach%20State%20was%20also%20changing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20now-President%20Joe%20Biden%20won%20Georgia%20by%20roughly%2012%2C000%20votes%20over%20then-President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjoe-biden-wins-georgia-democratic-party-south-presidential-election-2020-11%5C%22%3Eflipping%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Deep%20South%20state%20into%20the%20Democratic%20column.%20And%20Biden%20won%20Athens-Clarke%20with%20a%20whopping%2070%25-28%25%20victory%2C%20posting%20a%20nearly%2022%2C000-vote%20margin%20over%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Democrats%20continue%20to%20make%20inroads%20in%20Atlanta%20and%20its%20populous%20suburbs%2C%20margins%20like%20those%20in%20Athens-Clarke%20will%20make%20the%20difference%20for%20both%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Democrats%20more%20aligned%20with%20most%20young%20votes%20on%20issues%20like%20voting%20rights%2C%20reproductive%20rights%2C%20student%20debt%20relief%2C%20climate%20change%2C%20and%20health%20care%20reform%2C%20the%20party%20has%20been%20able%20to%20cut%20into%20statewide%20margins%20to%20a%20degree%20that%20Republicans%20can%20no%20longer%20ignore%20if%20they%20want%20to%20remain%20viable%20as%20a%20party%20in%20key%20swing%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWisconsin%20is%20a%20similar%20scene.%20As%20one%20of%20the%20most%20politically-divided%20states%20in%20the%20country%2C%20even%20a%20slight%20shift%20in%20votes%20can%20affect%20statewide%20vote%20totals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Trump%20won%20Wisconsin%20by%20less%20than%201%20percent%20of%20the%20vote.%20Four%20years%20later%2C%20Biden%20also%20won%20the%20state%20by%20less%20than%201%20percent%20of%20the%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20last%20year%2C%20GOP%20Sen.%20Ron%20Johnson%20won%20reelection%20to%20a%20third%20term%20over%20then-Democratic%20Lt.%20Gov.%20Mandela%20Barnes%2C%20but%20the%20race%20was%20decided%20by%20roughly%2027%2C000%20votes%20%E2%80%94%20or%201%20percentage%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMadison%20%E2%80%94%20the%20capital%20of%20Wisconsin%20and%20home%20to%20the%20flagship%20University%20of%20Wisconsin%20campus%20%E2%80%94%20has%20continued%20to%20attract%20new%20residents%2C%20fueling%20Democratic%20margins%20in%20fast-growing%20Dane%20County.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202000%2C%20Gore%20won%20Wisconsin%20by%20less%20than%206%2C000%20votes%20(48.8%25-48.6%25)%20and%20won%20Dane%20by%20nearly%2067%2C000%20votes%20(61%25-33%25)%20over%20Bush.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2020%20years%20later%2C%20the%20Democratic%20coalition%20had%20shifted%20to%20one%20driven%20by%20urban%20and%20suburban%20voters.%20In%202020%2C%20Biden%20won%20Wisconsin%20by%20roughly%2020%2C000%20votes%20(49.45%25-48.8%25)%20while%20he%20romped%20in%20Dane%2C%20winning%20the%20county%20with%20a%20181%2C000-vote%20edge%20(75%25-23%25)%20over%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20Trump's%20strength%20in%20many%20of%20the%20state's%20rural%20areas%2C%20Biden%20performed%20well%20enough%20in%20Dane%20and%20Milwaukee%20counties%20to%20flip%20Wisconsin%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20Republican%20strategist%20Mark%20Graul%20%E2%80%94%20who%20ran%20Bush's%202004%20campaign%20operation%20in%20Wisconsin%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2Fmagazine%2F2023%2F07%2F21%2Fgop-college-towns-00106974%5C%22%3Etold%20Politico%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20developments%20present%20a%20major%20challenge%20for%20the%20GOP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20really%20big%20deal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20outlet.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20Democrats%20are%20doing%20in%20Dane%20County%20is%20truly%20making%20it%20impossible%20for%20Republicans%20to%20win%20a%20statewide%20race.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Csection%3E%3Caside%20data-aside-index%3D%5C%223%5C%22%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frepublicans-throttled-college-towns-democrats-swing-states-millennials-gen-z-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdi