ers%20to%20serve%20alcohol.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELegislators%20in%20Wisconsin%20are%20pushing%20to%20lower%20the%20alcohol%20service%20age%20from%2018%20to%2014%20years%20old.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBars%20in%20various%20states%20across%20the%20country%20may%20be%20staffed%20by%20high%20schoolers%20as%20more%20lawmakers%20and%20businesses%20push%20to%20lower%20the%20legal%20age%20to%20serve%20alcohol%20and%20bartend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20at%20least%20nine%20states%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Iowa%2C%20Michigan%2C%20Ohio%2C%20Kentucky%2C%20West%20Virginia%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20Alabama%2C%20Wisconsin%2C%20and%20Idaho%20%E2%80%94%20that%20have%20enacted%20or%20introduced%20laws%20that%20would%20allow%20minors%20ages%2014%20to%2017%20to%20serve%20alcohol%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Fblog%2Falcohol-service-age%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20report%20from%20Economic%20Policy%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20has%20been%20gaining%20traction%20since%202021%20as%20businesses%20and%20lawmakers%20seek%20solutions%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwisconsin-republicans-want-14-year-olds-to-serve-alcohol-2023-5%3F_gl%3D1*1ggwv2a*_ga*NDk0OTkwMDg3LjE2NTQ3MDM2MDA.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY5MDEzNDYxNS42NjkuMS4xNjkwMTM0Nzk1LjI1LjAuMA..%5C%22%3Ean%20ongoing%20labor%20shortage.%3C%2Fa%3E%20In%20April%2C%20Iowa's%20Republican-led%20state%20senate%20voted%2032-17%20to%20pass%20a%20bill%20rolling%20back%20child%20labor%20laws%20in%20the%20state.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fiowa-gop-senate-votes-weaken-child-labor-laws-2023-4%5C%22%3EThe%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20allow%20teens%20to%20work%20until%209%3A00%20p.m.%20during%20the%20school%20year%20and%20until%2011%3A00%20p.m.%20over%20the%20summer%20and%20serve%20alcohol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20restaurant%20industry%20is%20backing%20legislators%20in%20their%20effor