0father%20and%20placing%20the%20wrong%20body%20in%20his%20burial%20clothes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%C2%A0Clifford%20Zaner%20died%20of%20heart%20failure%20at%20his%C2%A0South%20Carolina%C2%A0home%20on%20February%2025%2C%20at%20the%20age%20of%2072.%20He%20told%20his%20family%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20be%20buried%20in%20black%20jeans%20and%20his%20favorite%20Led%20Zeppelin%20T-shirt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20he%20died%2C%20his%20body%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20shipped%20to%20New%20York.%20However%2C%20the%20wrong%20man%20was%20sent%20and%20then%20buried%20in%20their%20father's%20favourite%20clothes.%20The%20sisters%20noticed%20something%20was%20wrong%20when%20they%20asked%20to%20see%20their%20father%20one%20last%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20knew%20something%20was%20wrong%20the%20day%20of%20the%20funeral.%20There%20were%20red%20flags%20when%20we%20viewed%20the%20body%2C%20huge%20red%20flags.%20The%20first%20thing%20I%20noticed%20when%20they%20opened%20the%20casket%20was%20no%20mustache%E2%80%A6%20The%20first%20thing%20I%20saw%20was%20just%20a%20bare%20upper%20lip%2C%20and%20I%20couldn't%20stop%20focusing%20on%20that%2C''%C2%A0Stacy%20Holzman%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailybeast.com%2Fthe-wrong-man-was-buried-in-clifford-zaners-led-zeppelin-shirt-and-grave-lawsuit%3Fref%3Dscroll%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Daily%20Beast%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20had%20stitches%20across%20his%20forehead%2C%20indicating%20that%20an%20autopsy%20had%20been%20performed%2C%20while%20Mr.%20Zaner%20hadn't%20undergone%20any%20such%20procedure.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Star%20of%20David%20Memorial%20Chapel%20funeral%20home%20insisted%20that%20the%20body%20belonged%20to%20Ms.%20Holzman's%20father%20and%20assured%20them%20that%20they%20received%20the%20correct%20body%20from%20Fletcher%20Funeral%20Service%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20deeply%20regret%20any%20sorrow%20experienced%20by%20the%20family%20for%20the%20mistake%20made%20by%20the%20funeral%20home%20in%20South%20Carolina%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20funeral%20home%20said.%20It%20also%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cfamilies%20are%20under%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20stress%20when%20they%20identify%20their%20deceased.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20after%20three%20weeks%2C%20the%20funeral%20home%20informed%20Mr.%20Zaner's%20family%20that%20there%20had%20indeed%20been%20a%20mix-up.%20A%20second%20funeral%20with%20the%20correct%20remains%20was%20then%20held%20in%20Jacksonville%2C%20on%20March%2024%2C%20but%20without%20his%20favourite%20T-shirt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sisters%2C%20meanwhile%20claim%20to%20have%20not%20received%20a%20refund%20for%20the%20first%20funeral%20with%20the%20Star%20of%20David%20that%20involved%20the%20wrong%20remains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20is%20hoping%20a%20%2460%20million%20lawsuit%20will%20send%20a%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20them%20to%20take%20responsibility%20for%20this%20horrible%20mistake.%20And%20I%20do%20want%20things%20put%20in%20place%20in%20the%20future%2C%20which%20I%20think%20should%20have%20been%20there%2C%20from%20happening%20to%20anybody%20else%2C''%20Megan%20Zaner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690135260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F94up5t78_casket_625x300_23_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-sisters-file-60-million-lawsuit-after-funeral-home-buries-stranger-in-their-fathers-grave-4234830%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20sisters%20have%20accused%20the%20funeral%20homes%20of%20mistaking%20another%20person's%20remains%20for%20their%20father's%20and%20placing%20the%20wrong%20body%20in%20his%20burial%20clothes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-sisters-file-60-million-laws