ts%20movement%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20White%20House%20official%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%201955%2C%20Emmett%20Till%20was%20accused%20by%20Carolyn%20Bryant%20Donham%20of%20making%20improper%20advances%20toward%20her%20while%20he%20was%20inside%20the%20Bryant's%20Grocery%20and%20Meat%20Market%20in%20Money%2C%20Miss.%2C%20which%20at%20the%20time%20was%20run%20by%20Donham%20and%20her%20then-husband%2C%20Roy%20Bryant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20accusation%20prompted%20Bryant%20and%20his%20half-brother%2C%20J.%20W.%20Milam%2C%20to%20abduct%20Till%20at%20gunpoint%20from%20the%20home%20of%20his%20great-uncle%2C%20Moses%20Wright.%20Bryant%20and%20Milam%20then%20tortured%20and%20lynched%20the%20teenager%20before%20throwing%20his%20body%20into%20the%20Tallahatchie%20River.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETill's%20battered%20body%20was%20weighed%20down%20by%20a%20cotton-gin%20fan%20and%20was%20found%20several%20days%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20face%20was%20left%20unrecognizable.%20But%2C%20at%20his%20funeral%20service%20in%20Chicago%2C%20Mamie%20Till-Mobley%20insisted%20that%20her%20son%20would%20have%20an%20open%20casket%20funeral%20so%20the%20world%20could%20see%20the%20brutality%20and%20horror%20of%20what%20her%20son%20endured%20in%20the%20segregated%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Illinois%20monument%20site%20will%20be%20the%20Roberts%20Temple%20Church%20of%20God%20in%20Christ%20in%20the%20Bronzeville%20neighborhood%20of%20Chicago%2C%20on%20the%20city's%20South%20Side%2C%20where%20Emmett%20Till's%20funeral%20was%20held%20in%201955.%20The%20Mississippi%20sites%20include%20Graball%20Landing%2C%20where%20it%20is%20believed%20that%20Till's%20body%20was%20recovered%20from%20the%20Tallahatchie%20River%2C%20and%20the%20Tallahatchie%20County%20Second%20District%20Courthouse%20in%20Sumner%2C%20where%20Bryant%20and%20Milam%20were%20tried%20and%20acquitted%20by%20an%20all-white%20jury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%201956%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pbs.org%2Fwgbh%2Famericanexperience%2Ffeatures%2Ftill-killers-confession%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Look%20magazine%2C%20Bryant%20and%20Milam%20confessed%20to%20the%20murder.%20Both%20men%20have%20since%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDonham%20died%20in%20April.%20She%20was%2088%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20December%2C%20Congress%20voted%20to%20award%20the%20Congressional%20Gold%20Medal%20posthumously%20to%20Till%20and%20his%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202022%2C%20Biden%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-anti-lynching-legislation-law-federal-hate-crime-2022-3%5C%22%3Esigned%20into%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Emmett%20Till%20Anti-Lynching%20Act%2C%20which%20made%20lynching%20a%20federal%20hate%20crime%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20US%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20president's%20push%20to%20elevate%20civil%20rights%20leaders%20and%20acknowledge%20the%20full%20scope%20of%20Black%20history%20comes%20as%20Republicans%20in%20recent%20years%20have%20sought%20to%20limit%20how%20race%20can%20be%20taught%20in%20classrooms%2C%20with%20conservatives%20also%20targeting%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20programs%20and%20hailing%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20recent%20decision%20to%20end%20affirmative%20action%20in%20college%20admissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden's%20original%20student%20debt%20relief%20plan%2C%20which%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-blocked-supreme-court-strikes-down-debt-cancellation-2023-5%5C%22%3Einvalidated%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20was%20also%20intended%20to%20be%20one%20that%20had%20a%20significant%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2022%2F08%2F24%2Ffact-sheet-president-biden-announces-student-loan-relief-for-borrowers-who-need-it-most%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eracial%20equity%20ele