20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.worldbank.org%2Findicator%2FSL.TLF.CACT.FE.ZS%3Flocations%3DIN-8S-BD-Z4-XQ%5C%22%3E26%25%20of%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20South%20Asia%20are%20economically%20active%2C%20i.e.%2C%20they%20are%20either%20working%20or%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20as%20compared%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.worldbank.org%2Findicator%2FSL.TLF.CACT.MA.ZS%3Flocations%3DIN-8S-BD-Z4-XQ%5C%22%3E75%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImagine%20the%20impact%20on%20the%20economy%20if%20the%20ratio%20for%20women%20employment%20converged%20to%20that%20of%20men.%20The%20International%20Labour%20Organisation%20estimates%20that%20reducing%20the%20gap%20in%20labour%20force%20participation%20rates%20between%20men%20and%20women%20by%2025%25%20by%202025%20could%20raise%20the%20global%20gross%20domestic%20product%20(GDP)%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fwcmsp5%2Fgroups%2Fpublic%2F---ed_dialogue%2F---act_emp%2Fdocuments%2Fpublication%2Fwcms_735949.pdf%5C%22%3E3.9%25%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fwcmsp5%2Fgroups%2Fpublic%2F---ed_dialogue%2F---act_emp%2Fdocuments%2Fpublication%2Fwcms_735949.pdf%5C%22%3E%245.8%20trillion%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Asian%20countries%2C%20because%20of%20their%20population%20and%20low%20levels%20of%20female%20participation%2C%20can%20reap%20incredible%20gains%20from%20levelling%20their%20gender%20gaps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gender%20of%20managers%20and%20employers%20is%20one%20of%20the%20important%20factors%20that%20influence%20women%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20from%20World%20Bank%20Enterprise%20Surveys%20(2021)%2C%20covering%20the%20formal%20sector%2C%20shows%20that%20women-led%20enterprises%20create%20more%20steady%20employment%20opportunities%20for%20women%20compared%20to%20those%20headed%20by%20men.%20In%20firms%20owned%20by%20men%2C%20the%20average%20share%20of%20women%20workers%20was%20found%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw28486%2Fw28486.pdf%5C%22%3E25%25%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20compared%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw28486%2Fw28486.pdf%5C%22%3E43%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20women-owned%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20women-owned%20firms%20are%20in%20a%20minority%2C%20globally.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.worldbank.org%2Findicator%2FIC.FRM.FEMO.ZS%3Flocations%3DIN-8S-BD-Z4-XQ-1W%5C%22%3EWorld%20Bank%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20the%20share%20of%20firms%20where%20a%20woman%20was%20among%20the%20principal%20owners%20was%20only%2018%25%20for%20South%20Asia%2C%20in%202021%2C%20as%20compared%20to%2033%25%20for%20the%20world%2C%20and%20over%2045%25%20for%20East%20Asia%20and%20the%20Pacific.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPromoting%20greater%20entrepreneurship%20among%20women%20is%20therefore%20critical.%20If%20successful%2C%20it%20could%20shape%20a%20very%20different%20economic%20and%20social%20trajectory%20for%20South%20Asia%20and%20its%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECreating%20an%20enabling%20environment%20for%20women-led%20firms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20can%20be%20done%20to%20change%20the%20status%20quo%2C%20and%20create%20an%20enabling%20environment%20for%20women-led%20small%20and%20medium%20enterprises%3F%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.india.talentnomics.org%2F_files%2Fugd%2F121f4c_711db581a81d418994fcd995e1e0355c.pdf%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%20by%20TalentNomics%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20Radhicka%20Kapoor%20as%20lead%20author%2C%20looked%20at%20the%20success%20differentiators%20for%2020%20first-generation%20women%20entrepreneurs%20in%20South%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20encapsulates%20the%20promise%20as%20well%20as%20the%20challenge%20of%20women%20entrepreneurship%20in%20South%20Asia%3A%20it%20was%20not%20easy%20to%20find%20first-generation%20women%20entrepreneurs%2C%20especially%20outside%20India%2C%20but%20their%20stories%20and%20efforts%20to%20overcome%20business%20and%20societal%20barriers%20are%20inspirational%20and%20worth%20learning%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDrawing%20from%20this%20study%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20few%20others%2C%20a%20holistic%20effort%20along%20the%20following%20dimensions%20could%20have%20a%20significant%2C%20if%20not%20immediate%2C%20impact%20on%20creating%20a%20larger%20pool%20of%20women-led%20enterprises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECollection%20of%20data%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20Gender%20analysis%20is%20the%20opposite%20of%20a%20framing%20that%20is%20gender%20blind%20or%20gender%20neutral.%20What%20gets%20measured%20gets%20done.%20Hence%2C%20it%20is%20vital%20to%20collect%20gender-disaggregated%20data.%20More%20granular%20data%20collection%20will%20allow%20policymakers%20to%20better%20assess%20the%20degree%20to%20which%20women-led%20SMEs%20contribute%20to%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20better%20understand%20barriers%20to%20gender%20equity%2C%20ultimately%20leading%20to%20more%20effective%20policy%20interventions%20and%20reforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEqual%20access%20to%20finance%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20Difficulties%20in%20accessing%20finance%20are%20often%20intensified%20by%20gender-related%20factors%20which%20include%20women%E2%80%99s%20lack%20of%20collateral%2C%20weak%20property%20rights%20and%20discriminatory%20regulations%2C%20laws%20and%20customs.%20The%20International%20Finance%20Corporation%20estimates%20that%20as%20many%20as%2070%25%20of%20women-owned%20SMEs%20in%20the%20formal%20sector%20in%20developing%20countries%20are%20unserved%20or%20underserved%20by%20financial%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20a%20financing%20gap%20of%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifc.org%2Fwps%2Fwcm%2Fconnect%2F44b004b2-ed46-48fc-8ade-aa0f485069a1%2FWomenOwnedSMes%2BReport-Final.pdf%3FMOD%3DAJPERES%26CVID%3DkiiZZDZ%5C%22%3E%24285%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20government%20and%20private%20programmes%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mudra.org.in%2F%5C%22%3EPradhan%20Mantri%20Mudra%20Yojana%20(PMMY)%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India%2C%20facilitate%20easier%20access%20to%20institutional%20credit%20for%20women-led%20micro-enterprises%2C%20more%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20to%20educate%20women%20entrepreneurs%20about%20the%20full%20range%20of%20financial%20instruments%20and%20digital%20finance%20technologies%20through%20targeted%20informational%20campaigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20supply%20side%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.briefindia.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FPolicy-Brief-Womens-Inclusion-in-Indias-Trade-Ecosystem-From-Talk-to-Action_By-Nikita-Singla.pdf%5C%22%3Ereforms%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20needed%20in%20the%20financial%20sector%20to%20enable%20them%20to%20lend%20more%20to%20women-led%20SMEs%2C%20such%20as%20implementing%20alternative%20credit%20scoring%20options%20to%20replace%20the%20requirement%20for%20collateral%2C%20utilising%20trading%20history%20from%20digital%20platforms%2C%20or%20compiling%20a%20score%20based%20on%20cash%20flow%20analysis%2C%20household%20income%20and%20behavioural%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20gender-balanced%20staffing%20within%20financial%20institutions%20can%20also%20help%20address%20the%20societal%20bias%20and%20scepticism%20towards%20women-owned%20enterprises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExpansion%20of%20mentorship%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldbank.org%2Fen%2Ftopic%2Fgender%2Fpublication%2Fbreaking-barriers-female-entrepreneurs-who-cross-over-to-male-dominated-sectors%5C%22%3EWorld%20Bank%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20female%20entrepreneurs%20who%20cross%20over%20into%20male-dominated%20sectors%20perform%20better%20than%20those%20who%20remain%20in%20traditionally%20female-concentrated%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESector%20choice%20is%20certainly%20one%20of%20the%20factors%20that%20contributes%20to%20the%20gap%20in%20men%20versus%20women%20entrepreneur%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20support%20from%20donor%20agencies%20and%20tie-ups%20with%20non-profit%20organisations%20like%20Mann%20Deshi%20Foundation%20and%20TalentNomics%20India%20%E2%80%93%20that%20have%20expertise%20in%20conducting%20mentorship%20programmes%20%E2%80%93%20successive%20generations%20of%20women%20entrepreneurs%20can%20be%20mentored%20and%20supported%20to%20cross%20over%20into%20male-dominated%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20effective%20mentoring%20programme%20would%20incorporate%20a%20sustained%20period%20of%20learning%2C%20one-on-one%20mentor%20connect%2C%20and%20as%20icing%20on%20the%20cake%2C%20connect%20the%20mentee%20with%20a%20mentor%20(man%20or%20woman)%20who%20is%20successful%20in%20a%20male-dominated%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERole%20models%20also%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20developing%20the%20entrepreneurial%20spirit%2C%20as%20Marian%20Wright%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eputs%20it%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20what%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20see.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Asia%20can%20learn%20from%20global%20best%20practices.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oecd-ilibrary.org%2Fwomen-ambassadors-sweden_5jlz6rjc6p9n.pdf%3FitemId%3D%252Fcontent%252Fcomponent%252F9789264251496-23-en%26mimeType%3Dpdf%5C%22%3EWomen%E2%80%99s%20Entrepreneurship%20Ambassadors%20Programme%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Sweden%20engages%20volunteer%20role%20models%20to%20participate%20in%20public%20events%20and%20speak%20at%20schools%20and%20universities.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechnovationchallenge.org%2F%5C%22%3ETechnovation%20Girls%20programme%3C%2Fa%3E%20enables%20girls%20in%20over%20100%20countries%20to%20work%20with%20female%20mentors%20to%20launch%20technology%20start-ups%20aimed%20at%20addressing%20a%20problem%20they%20have%20identified%20in%20their%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESupporting%20women%E2%80%99s%20transition%20to%20higher%20levels%20of%20trade%20value%20chains%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbit.ly%2F2HOpD6V%5C%22%3EResearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20World%20Bank%20on%20different%20value%20chains%20in%20North%20East%20India%2C%20including%20spices%2C%20bamboo%2C%20horticulture%20and%20medical%20tourism%2C%20shows%20that%20the%20participation%20of%20women%20is%20higher%20in%20some%20segments%20of%20the%20value%20chain%2C%20such%20as%20cultivation%20and%20harvesting%20in%20agriculture%2C%20and%20more%20generally%2C%20in%20sorting%2C%20grading%2C%20packaging%20and%20labelling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20enabling%20women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20different%20value%20chains%2C%20these%20activities%20are%20often%20less%20remunerative%20for%20workers%20compared%20to%20others%2C%20such%20as%20R%26amp%3BD%2C%20production%2C%20distribution%2C%20marketing%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGaps%20in%20education%2C%20skills%20and%20training%20undermine%20women%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20engage%20in%20and%20move%20up%20to%20higher-value%20activities.%20Addressing%20these%20gaps%20could%20be%20a%20fruitful%20endeavour%20for%20development%20partners%2C%20working%20in%20tandem%20with%20state%20governments.%20Training%2C%20including%20on-the-job%20training%2C%20could%20usefully%20focus%20on%20areas%20such%20as%20business%20development%2C%20quality%20control%2C%20marketing%2C%20distribution%2C%20access%20to%20finance%20and%20the%20ability%20to%20use%20higher-grade%20agricultural%20inputs%20and%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20training%20would%20not%20only%20help%20enhance%20women%20entrepreneurship%2C%20but%20also%20help%20women%20to%20transition%20to%20more%20remunerative%20segments%20of%20value%20chains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAddressing%20regressive%20gender%20norms%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20Regressive%20gender%20norms%20often%20become%20embedded%20in%20discriminatory%20laws%20and%20regulations%2C%20especially%20evidenced%20in%20unequal%20property%20and%20inheritance%20rights.%20In%20turn%2C%20these%20laws%20impede%20women%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20start%20and%20grow%20businesses%2C%20as%20fixed%20assets%20are%20the%20most%20readily%20accepted%20form%20of%20collateral%20for%20commercial%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20South%20Asia%2C%20asset%20ownership%2C%20especially%20land%20ownership%2C%20is%20primarily%20determined%20by%20inheritance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInheritance%20rights%20over%20parental%20and%20spousal%20property%20have%20been%20equalised%20between%20men%20and%20women%20in%20Bhutan%2C%20India%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20and%20Nepal%2C%20while%20unequal%20inheritance%20rights%20are%20still%20prevalent%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20Maldives%2C%20and%20Pakistan.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblogs.worldbank.org%2Fdevelopmenttalk%2Fwomens-legal-rights-and-gender-gaps-property-ownership-developing-countries%5C%22%3EResearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20the%20gender%20gaps%20in%20property%20ownership%20in%20South%20Asia%20are%20large%20by%20global%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvidence%20suggests%20that%20the%20use%20of%20economic%20incentives%2C%20in%20the%20form%20of%20transfers%2C%20subsidies%2C%20and%20access%20to%20financial%20instruments%20can%20also%20make%20a%20difference%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20such%20norms.%20Large-scale%20interventions%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frepository.gheli.harvard.edu%2Frepository%2F10669%2F%5C%22%3EPakistan%E2%80%99s%20Punjab%20Female%20Secondary%20School%20Stipend%20(FSSS)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20conditional%20cash%20transfer%20programme%20for%20adolescent%20girls%20to%20stay%20in%20school%2C%20have%20resulted%20in%20gains%20in%20education%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20a%20mindset%20on%20a%20later%20age%20for%20marriage.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fevaw-global-database.unwomen.org%2Fen%2Fcountries%2Fasia%2Findia%2F2005%2Fthe-hindu-succession-amendment-act-2005%5C%22%3EAmendments%20to%20the%20Hindu%20Succession%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20granted%20daughters%20equal%20rights%20to%20inherit%20ancestral%20property%2C%20is%20another%20important%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupport%20for%20women%E2%80%99s%20entrepreneurship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20these%20changes%20is%20easy%2C%20because%20the%20barriers%2C%20like%20most%20gender%20issues%2C%20stem%20from%20biases%20and%20attitudes%20prevalent%20for%20thousands%20of%20years.%20But%20all%20are%20amenable%20to%20change%2C%20even%20if%20the%20results%20will%20take%20longer%20in%20some%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20devising%20a%20plan%20of%20action%20to%20deliver%20entrepreneurship%20support%20to%20women%2C%20one%20of%20the%20key%20questions%20is%20whether%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20delivered%20through%20dedicated%20women-only%20programmes%20by%20specialist%20agencies%2C%20or%20could%20it%20be%20integrated%20into%20mainstream%20programmes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobally%2C%20both%20approaches%20are%20in%20use%2C%20with%20the%20choice%20being%20eventually%20determined%20by%20social%20attitudes%20towards%20women%20in%20society%20and%20the%20labour%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20developed%20countries%2C%20where%20women%20face%20fewer%20challenges%20in%20accessing%20education%20and%20jobs%2C%20support%20for%20women%E2%80%99s%20entrepreneurship%20is%20delivered%20largely%20through%20mainstream%20programmes.%20However%2C%20in%20South%20Asia%2C%20given%20the%20particularly%20challenging%20environment%20for%20women%20entrepreneurs%2C%20there%20may%20be%20a%20preference%20for%20dedicated%20women%E2%80%99s%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHopefully%2C%20when%20there%20is%20a%20repeat%20study%20of%20first-generation%20women%20entrepreneurs%20in%20South%20Asia%2C%20say%2C%20at%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20decade%2C%20the%20ecosystem%20would%20have%20become%20more%20supportive%2C%20fostering%20the%20growth%20of%20many%20more%20inspiring%20female%20entrepreneurs%20like%20Nayana%20Karunaratne%20of%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20Huma%20Fakhar%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Surakchya%20Adhikari%20from%20Nepal%2C%20Siffat%20Sarwar%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20Karma%20Yogini%20from%20Bhutan%2C%20Zoona%20Naseem%20from%20the%20Maldives%2C%20or%20Ruchika%20Bhuwalka%20from%20India.%20(For%20the%20complete%20list%2C%20see%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.india.talentnomics.org%2F_files%2Fugd%2F121f4c_711db581a81d418994fcd995e1e0355c.pdf%5C%22%3ETalentNomics%20India%20study%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESanjay%20Kathuria%20is%20a%20Senior%20Visiting%20Fellow%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20Policy%20Research%3B%20Adjunct%20Professor%20at%20Georgetown%20and%20Ashoka%20Universities%3B%20and%20Global%20Fellow%20at%20Wilson%20Center.%20He%20tweets%20%40%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSanjay_1818%5C%22%3ESanjay_1818%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENikita%20Singla%20is%20Associate%20Director%20at%20the%20New%20Delhi-based%20Bureau%20of%20Research%20on%20Industry%20and%20Economic%20Fundamentals.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690106429000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F22181409%2Fimage-1163.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fsouth-asia-can-reap-incredible-gains-by-empowering-first-generation-women-entrepreneurs%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Providing%20access%20to%20finance%2C%20mentorship%2C%20supporting%20transition%20to%20higher%20value%20chains%2C%20etc.%20could%20help%20in%20creating%20an%20enabling%20environment%20for%20women-led%20firms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fsouth-asia-can-reap-incredible-gains-by-empowering-first-generation-women-entrepreneurs%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sudha%20Murty%3A%20I%20cried%20after%20watching%20Raazi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690105273000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102054883%2Cimg