d%20acute%20kidney%20injury%20among%20children%20and%20led%20to%20the%20death%20of%2070%20of%20them%20in%20the%20country%20last%20year.%20Most%20of%20them%20were%20younger%20than%20two%20years%20old.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20task%20force%20had%20started%20an%20inquiry%20in%20November%20last%20year%20and%20submitted%20its%20report%20in%20March%20this%20year.%20The%20Gambian%20government%20released%20it%20on%20July%2021%20and%20issued%20a%20statement%20regarding%20its%20response%20to%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendations.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20a%20copy%20of%20both%20the%20task%20force%20report%20and%20the%20government%20statement.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20task%20force%20has%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Government%20of%20The%20Gambia%20through%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Justice%20should%20forthwith%20explore%20the%20possibility%20of%20instituting%20legal%20action%20against%20Atlantic%20Pharmaceuticals%20%5Bimporter%5D%2C%20Maiden%20Pharmaceuticals%20%5BIndian%20manufacturer%5D%2C%20and%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20to%20seek%20redress%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20families%20of%20the%20victims%20of%20AKI%20%5Bacute%20kidney%20injury%5D%20outbreak.%E2%80%9D%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Gambian%20government%20has%20accepted%20the%20recommendation%20as%20far%20as%20initiating%20a%20legal%20action%20against%20Maiden%20Pharmaceuticals%2C%20the%20Indian-based%20drug%20manufacturer%2C%20and%20Atlantic%20Pharmaceuticals%2C%20the%20US-based%20importer%20which%20procured%20the%20drugs%20from%20the%20Indian%20manufacturer%20for%20Gambia.%20It%20has%20said%20it%20has%20engaged%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctop%20tier%20international%20law%20firm%E2%80%9D%20for%20legal%20advice.%20The%20statement%20did%20not%20say%20anything%2C%20though%2C%20about%20taking%20legal%20action%20against%20the%20Indian%20government.%20It%20said%20the%20Gambian%20government%20would%20%E2%80%9Cengage%E2%80%9D%20with%20its%20Indian%20counterpart.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20what%20that%20engagement%20will%20yield%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20the%20fifth%20scientific%20report%20to%20come%20to%20a%20conclusion%20that%20the%20India-based%20firm%E2%80%99s%20products%20were%20contaminated%20with%20highly%20toxic%20chemicals%20%E2%80%93%20diethylene%20glycol%20(DEG)%20and%20ethylene%20glycol%20(EG).%20However%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20has%20plainly%20refused%20to%20acknowledge%20any%20role%20of%20the%20Indian%20firm%2C%20if%20its%20reaction%20to%20the%20previous%20four%20reports%20are%20anything%20to%20go%20by.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20reports%20were%20made%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Findian-firm-culpable-for-kidney-injuries-linked-to-death-of-70-children-gambia-parliament-probe-says%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGambian%20parliamentary%20committee%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fgambia-cough-syrup-deaths-us-cdc%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EUS%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20(CDC)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20and%20a%20team%20of%20international%20experts%20that%20published%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fglobal-experts-causality-assessment-confirms-indian-cough-syrups-led-to-child-deaths-in-gambia%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecausality%20assessment%20report%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20earliest%20proof%20of%20drugs%20being%20contaminated%20in%20very%20high%20amounts%20came%20in%20the%20form%20of%20results%20from%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fexclusive-who-lab-report-deg-contamination-cough-syrups-gambia-deaths%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESwitzerland-based%20lab%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20where%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%20had%20sent%20samples%20for%20testing%20in%20September%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20participating%20in%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FANI%2Fstatus%2F1677933879423012864%3Ft%3DlAAgy5-8tYYKmRFPXN76fg%26s%3D08%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epodcast%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20hosted%20by%20ANI%20editor%20Smita%20Prakash%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20health%20minister%20Mansukh%20Mandaviya%20had%20said%20there%20was%20no%20evidence%20to%20suggest%20contamination%20led%20to%20deaths.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20will%20be%20surprised%20to%20know%20that%20the%20children%20suffered%20from%20diarrhoea%20and%20they%20were%20given%20cough%20syrups%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMandaviya%20made%20this%20statement%20despite%20two%20reports%20%E2%80%93%20one%20by%20the%20US%20CDC%20and%20another%20by%20the%20Gambia%20parliamentary%20committee%20%E2%80%93%20last%20year%20saying%20that%20diarrhoea%20had%20no%20role%20to%20play%20in%20the%20deaths%20of%20the%20children.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F642595%2Fgambia-cough-syrup-deaths-us-cdc%2F%5C%22%3EUS%20CDC%E2%80%99s%20Report%20Is%20Third%20to%20Link%20Gambia%20Kids%E2%80%99%20Deaths%20to%20Cough%20Syrups%20Made%20by%20Indian%20Firm%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20task%20force%20report%20has%20offered%20by%20far%20the%20most%20detailed%20explanation%20about%20why%20diarrhoea%20was%20not%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20deaths%20of%20the%20children.%20It%20was%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.ph%2FQKAhN%23selection-1405.110-1405.122%5C%22%3ENovember%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20media%20report%20published%20the%20first%20plausible%20statements%20emerging%20from%20Gambia%20linking%20E.%20coli%2C%20a%20bacterial%20infection%20causing%20diarrhoea%2C%20with%20the%20deaths.%20The%20Indian%20government%20also%20alluded%20to%20this%20%E2%80%98media%20report%E2%80%99%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDDNewslive%2Fstatus%2F1603636447520739332%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%257Ctwcamp%255Etweetembed%257Ctwterm%255E1603636447520739332%257Ctwgr%255Ecafcb523ef7d193795584fbe14a656bd0a395ab5%257Ctwcon%255Es1_%26ref_url%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fthewire.in%252Fhealth%252Fglobal-experts-causality-assessment-confirms-indian-cough-syrups-led-to-child-deaths-in-gambia%5C%22%3Eletter%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewritten%20to%20the%20WHO%20last%20December%20in%20this%20case%20wherein%20it%20had%20said%20nothing%20was%20wrong%20with%20the%20drugs%20exported%20to%20Gambia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0It%20is%20important%20to%20note%20here%20as%20to%20who%20made%20that%20statement%20on%20the%20purported%20behalf%20of%20Gambia%20and%20was%20quoted%20in%20the%20media.%20It%20was%20Tijan%20Jallow%2C%20a%20staff%20member%20of%20the%20Gambia%E2%80%99s%20drug%20regulator%2C%20Medicines%20Control%20Agency%20(MCA).%20Jallow%E2%80%99s%20statement%20was%20quoted%20as%20that%20of%20the%20MCA%20in%20the%20said%20media%20report%2C%20though%20he%20is%20just%20a%20staff%20member%20(and%20not%20a%20senior%20official).%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20also%20repeated%20his%20stance%20before%20the%20task%20force%20in%20his%20interview%20and%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cdiseases%20associated%20with%20flooding%E2%80%9D%20could%20have%20contributed%20to%20the%20deaths.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20this%20current%20report%20hints%20at%20a%20potential%20conflict%20of%20interest%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Jallow%20as%20he%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ecurrently%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20supervising%20pharmacist%20of%20Atlantic%20Pharmaceuticals%20%E2%80%93%20the%20company%20which%20purchased%20drugs%20from%20Maiden%20pharmaceuticals%20and%20sent%20them%20to%20Gambia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20supervising%20pharmacist%20working%20with%20importers%2C%20one%20is%20supposed%20to%20provide%20professional%20advice%20to%20the%20importer%20%E2%80%9Cduring%20the%20process%20of%20importation%20and%20distribution%20of%20medicines%20and%20related%20products.%E2%80%9D%20Under%20the%20Gambian%20law%20it%20is%20legit%20for%20an%20MCA%20member%20to%2C%20simultaneously%2C%C2%A0%20take%20up%20a%20job%20at%20a%20private%20supervising%20pharmacist%20provided%20there%20is%20a%20formal%20declaration%20to%20that%20effect.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20be%20clear%20here%2C%20Jallow%20was%20not%20the%20supervising%20pharmacist%20for%20the%20Atlantic%20Pharmaceuticals%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhen%20the%20import%20took%20place%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20it%20was%20one%20Sait%20Kebbeh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKebbeh%2C%20like%20Jallow%2C%20also%20doubled%20as%20a%20staff%20member%20of%20Gambia%E2%80%99s%20drug%20regulator.%20And%20just%20like%20Jallow%2C%20Kebbeh%20also%20told%20the%20task%20force%20that%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20think%20the%20drugs%20were%20responsible.%20Instead%20some%20other%20infection%20could%20have%20also%20caused%20the%20deaths%2C%20he%20had%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20role%20as%20supervising%20pharmacist%20for%20Atlantic%20Pharmaceuticals%2C%20Kebbeh%20cleared%20the%20decks%20for%20it%20and%20through%20it%2C%20for%20exporting%20Maiden-made%20syrups%20to%20Gambia.%20He%20accepted%20before%20the%20task%20force%20that%20he%20provided%20technical%20support%20and%20the%20go-ahead%20to%20Atlantic%20pharma%20for%20import%20without%20making%20background%20checks%20on%20the%20Maiden%20Pharmaceuticals.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20such%2C%20the%20task%20force%20recommended%20disciplinary%20action%20against%20him%20which%20the%20Gambian%20government%20has%20accepted.%20It%20has%20referred%20his%20case%20to%20the%20Pharmacy%20Council%20for%20necessary%20action.%20It%20also%20recommended%20that%20the%20Gambian%20government%20make%20rules%20to%20prevent%20any%20such%20future%20conflict%20of%20interest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F654727%2Fglobal-experts-causality-assessment-confirms-indian-cough-syrups-led-to-child-deaths-in-gambia%2F%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Experts%E2%80%99%20Causality%20Assessment%20Confirms%20Indian%20Cough%20Syrups%20Led%20to%20Child%20Deaths%20in%20Gambia%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EExperts%E2%80%99%20opinion%20on%20causes%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20task%20force%20interviewed%20clinical%20and%20pharmaceutical%20experts%20to%2C%20just%20like%20the%20previous%20committee%20did%2C%20to%20go%20into%20the%20causes%20of%20deaths.%20Based%20on%20their%20interviews%20and%20previous%20reports%20the%20task%20force%20concluded%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Task%20Force%20finds%20it%20safe%20to%20conclude%2C%20without%20any%20qualms%2C%20that%20the%20death%20of%20the%20seventy%20children%20below%20the%20age%20of%20five%2C%20between%20July%20and%20October%202022%20related%20to%20Acute%20Kidney%20Injury%2C%20is%20as%20a%20direct%20result%20of%20contaminated%20medicines%20found%20in%20four%20cough%20and%20cold%20syrups%20imported%20by%20Atlantic%20Pharmacy%20from%20Maiden%20Pharmaceuticals%20Company%20Limited%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMuoneke%20Uzoamaka%20Vivian%2C%20a%20paediatric%20nephrologist%20at%20Gambia%E2%80%99s%20Edward%20Francis%20Small%20Teaching%20Hospital%20(EFSTH)%2C%20told%20the%20committee%20that%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20autopsies%20that%20she%20conducted%20and%20which%20revealed%20multi-organ%20failure%2C%20the%20same%20set%20of%20symptoms%20in%20children%20who%20died%2C%20observations%20made%20by%20her%20colleagues%20at%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20Nigeria%20and%20South%20Africa%2C%20and%20the%20initial%20lab%20results%20of%20medicines%20that%20she%20received%20and%20which%20had%20confirmed%20contamination%2C%20she%20%3C%2Fspan%3Ewas%3Cspan%3E%20convinced%20that%20the%20drugs%20were%20responsible%20for%20the%20deaths.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELater%2C%20WHO%20lab%20reports%20also%20confirmed%20Vivian%E2%80%99s%20findings%20as%20far%20as%20the%20contamination%20was%20concerned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20at%20the%20EFSTH%2C%20the%20hospital%20based%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20capital%2C%20Banjul%2C%20where%20the%20first%20cases%20of%20AKI%20outbreak%20landed%20in%20July%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20most%20important%20fact%20that%20made%20her%20conclude%20this%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20point%20after%20which%20the%20four%20medicines%20were%20withdrawn%20from%20the%20market%20following%20her%20recommendation%2C%20AKI%20cases%20drastically%20dropped%20in%20October%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERegarding%20diarrhoea%2C%20she%20said%2C%20in%20some%20children%20an%20infection%20of%20E.%20Coli%20bacteria%20was%20established.%20However%2C%20these%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20children%20who%20had%20landed%20at%20her%20hospital.%20They%20were%20children%20from%20the%20northern%20part%20of%20the%20country.%20The%20Gambian%20parliamentary%20committee%20report%20had%20also%20said%20exactly%20the%20same%20thing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20task%20force%20also%20interviewed%20Gabriel%20Ogun%2C%20a%20pathologist%20for%2022%20years%20and%20currently%20serving%20as%20head%20of%20lab%20at%20EFSTH.%20He%20told%20the%20committee%20that%20the%20probability%20of%20DEG%20and%20EG%20causing%20multiple%20organ%20failure%20in%20the%20children%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20revealed%20through%20autopsies%20%E2%80%93%20was%20%E2%80%9Cextremely%20high%E2%80%9D%20due%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20organ%20damage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20had%20said%20that%20no%20bacterial%20or%20viral%20infection%20could%20have%20manifested%20in%20that%20way%2C%20and%20thus%20ruled%20out%20an%20E.%20coli%20bacterial%20infection%20leading%20to%20diarrhoea%20%E2%80%93%20just%20like%20other%20committees%20did%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20task%20force%20committee%20also%20noted%20in%20the%20report%20that%20the%20expert%20opinions%20of%20Professor%20Vivian%2C%20Professor%20Ogun%20and%20Dr.%20Leigh%20of%20the%20EFSTH%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Cstrongly%20corroborated%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20report%20of%20the%20US-CDC%20and%20the%20causality%20assessment%20report%20made%20by%20a%20team%20of%20international%20experts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEver%20since%20the%20controversy%20erupted%20in%20October%20last%20year%2C%20Maiden%20Pharmaceuticals%20has%20consistently%20denied%20any%20wrongdoings%2C%20claiming%20its%20products%20were%20not%20tainted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20had%20also%20formed%20an%20expert%20committee%20of%20its%20own%20last%20year%20which%20cleared%20the%20name%20of%20the%20firm%20%E2%80%93%20though%20it%20did%20not%20come%20to%20any%20conclusion%20about%20diarrhoea%20causing%20deaths.%20The%20Indian%20government%20also%20never%20made%20its%20own%20report%20public.%20The%20WHO%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fwho-india-cough-syrup-gambia-expert-committee%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edid%20not%20accept%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20Indian%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20health%20minister%20also%20claimed%20in%20the%20podcast%20that%20the%20Indian%20government%20had%20made%20some%20correspondence%20with%20the%20Gambian%20government%20in%20this%20case%20to%20enquire%20about%20the%20details%20after%20the%20news%20of%20deaths%20of%20children%20surfaced.%20He%20did%20not%20clarify%20what%20the%20correspondence%20resulted%20in%2C%20and%20if%20and%20when%20it%20was%20done.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20minister%20went%20on%20to%20add%20in%20the%20podcast%20that%20out%20of%2023%20samples%20tested%2C%20India%20was%20told%2C%20only%20four%20failed.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20in%20one%20%5Bsame%5D%20batch%20of%20a%20drug%2C%20a%20few%20units%20fail%20the%20test%2C%20then%20all%20should%20and%20not%20just%20four%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20casting%20doubts%20over%20lab%20reports.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20fact%20remains%20that%20all%20the%20drugs%20tested%20were%20%3Ci%3Enot%3C%2Fi%3E%20from%20the%20same%20batch.%20Not%20only%20were%20they%20from%20the%20different%20batches%2C%20but%20in%20fact%20there%20were%20%3Ci%3E23%20%3C%2Fi%3Edifferent%20drugs%20altogether%20which%20were%20tested.%20%3Cem%3EFour%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20them%20failed%20the%20tests.%20They%20were%20Makoff%20Baby%20Cough%20Syrup%2C%20MaGrip%20N%20Cold%20syrup%2C%20Kofexmalin%20Baby%20Cough%20Syrup%20and%20Promethazine%20Oral%20solution.%20They%20could%20not%20have%20been%20from%20the%20same%20batch%20since%20they%20were%20different%20formulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20minister%E2%80%99s%20claims%20went%20unchecked%20in%20the%20podcast.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERole%20of%20the%20importer%3A%20Atlantic%20Pharma%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAtlantic%20Pharmaceuticals%20confessed%20to%20the%20task%20force%20that%20it%20did%20not%20run%20a%20detailed%20check%20into%20Maiden%20Pharmaceuticals%20beyond%20its%20officials%20visiting%20its%20site%20once%20in%20India%20before%20initiating%20the%20import.%20The%20US-based%20importer%20said%20it%20relied%20on%20the%20good%20manufacturing%20practices%20certificate%20that%20the%20Indian%20drug%20regulator%20had%20issued%20to%20Maiden%20Pharmaceuticals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Atlantic%20Pharmaceuticals%20did%20not%20find%20it%20necessary%20to%20look%20whether%20Maiden%20Pharmaceuticals%20had%20any%20past%20record%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fmaiden-pharma-gambia-cough-syrup-repeat-offender-substandard-drugs%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhich%2C%20indeed%2C%20Maiden%20had%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20Gujarat%20government%20had%20flagged%20substandard%20products%20of%20the%20company%20in%202015%20%E2%80%93%20as%20did%20the%20Kerala%20government.%20Their%20warnings%20were%20available%20in%20the%20public%20domain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdd%20to%20this%20the%20fact%20that%20Atlantic%20Pharmaceuticals%20also%20got%20another%20leeway%20from%20Gambia%E2%80%99s%20drug%20regulator.%20Usually%20a%20company%20has%20to%20be%20%E2%80%98registered%E2%80%99%20with%20Gambia%E2%80%99s%20drug%20regulator%20before%20importing%20medicines.%20The%20task%20force%20report%20has%20revealed%20that%20Atlantic%20pharma%20was%20merely%20%E2%80%98listed%E2%80%99%20and%20not%20%E2%80%98registered%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20process%20of%20listing%2C%20as%20explained%20to%20the%20inquiry%20committee%20by%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Gambia%E2%80%99s%20regulator%2C%20involved%20recording%20only%20the%20basic%20information%20of%20the%20product%20and%20supplier%2C%20to%20be%20utilised%20in%20the%20event%20of%20necessary%20recall.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20%E2%80%98registration%E2%80%99%20involves%20submission%20of%20a%20number%20of%20documents%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eprior%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20initiating%20the%20trade%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20importantly%2C%20the%20importer%20has%20to%20submit%20safety%20and%20efficacy%20of%20drugs%20being%20received%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20%E2%80%98listing%E2%80%99%20does%20not%20mandate%20this%20bit%20either.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20task%20force%20found%20that%20the%20executive%20director%20and%20deputy%20executive%20director%20of%20Gambia%E2%80%99s%20regulatory%20authority%20contradicted%20the%20Medicines%20and%20Related%20Products%20Act%202014%20and%20Regulation%202020%20laws%20of%20the%20country%20by%20allowing%20the%20%E2%80%98listing%E2%80%99%20process.%20And%20thus%2C%20it%20recommended%20their%20immediate%20removal%20and%20prosecution%20for%20%E2%80%9Cneglecting%20and%20abdicating%20their%20responsibilities%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Gambian%20government%20said%20in%20its%20statement%20on%20July%2021%20that%20the%20executive%20director%20has%20been%20dismissed%20with%20immediate%20effect%20and%20that%20the%20services%20of%20deputy%20director%20too%20have%20been%20terminated.%20For%20further%20legal%20action%2C%20the%20task%20force%20report%20has%20been%20sent%20to%20the%20Gambia%20police%20force.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Gambian%20government%20has%20also%20permanently%20revoked%20the%20licence%20of%20Atlantic%20Pharmaceuticals%20as%20well%20as%20has%20launched%20a%20legal%20suit%20against%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690099025000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F23131653%2FUntitled-design-5-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fgambia-cough-syrup-sue-indian-government%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20task%20force%2C%20which%20consisted%20of%20medical%20and%20other%20professionals%2C%20found%20the%20Indian%20firm%20Maiden%20Pharmaceuticals%20responsible%20for%20the%20deaths%20of%2070%20children.%20This%20is%20the%20fifth%20report%20to%20implicate%20the%20company.%20The%20Indian%20government%20has%20refused%20to%20accept%20the%20four%20previous%20reports.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A39%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fgambia-cough-syrup-sue-india