%80%9CFor%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20witnessed%20severe%20escalating%20attacks%20on%20religious%20minorities%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%A6%20And%20yet%20we%20know%20our%20own%20US%20State%20Department%20has%20yet%20to%20designate%20India%20as%20a%20Country%20of%20Particular%20Concern%20under%20US%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20as%20per%20a%20press%20release%20on%20the%20briefing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20bi-partisan%20US%20state-department%20funded%20US%20Commission%20on%20International%20Religious%20Freedom%20(USCIRF)%20has%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fuscirf-country-of-particular-concern-fourth-time%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erecommended%20for%20four%20consecutive%20years%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20India%20should%20be%20designated%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98Country%20of%20Particular%20Concern%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20State%20department.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETill%20now%2C%20the%20US%20state%20department%20has%20refused%20to%20take%20any%20such%20action.%20The%20Indian%20government%20has%20accused%20USCIRF%20of%20reiterating%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-lashes-out-uscirf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebiased%20and%20motivated%20comments%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20country%20in%20its%20annual%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20briefing%2C%20USCIRF%20Commissioner%20David%20Curry%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Commission%20had%20urged%20the%20Biden%20administration%20to%20raise%20religious%20freedom%20concerns%20during%20the%20Indian%20PM%E2%80%99s%20state%20visit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CReligious%20freedom%20was%20mentioned%20briefly%20during%20the%20visit%20but%20was%20certainly%20not%20a%20focal%20point%E2%80%A6%20Modi%20denied%20that%20discrimination%20of%20religious%20minorities%20existed%20in%20India.%20We%20strongly%20disagree%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20as%20quoted%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconta.cc%2F3PYKTHO%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epress%20communique%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20the%20organisers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20PM%20had%20been%20asked%20a%20question%20about%20the%20state%20of%20minorities%20at%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fbiden-by-his-side-modi-cites-constitution-to-parry-question-on-minority-rights-suppression-of-dissent%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erare%20press%20interaction%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20White%20House.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fspeeches-remarks%2F2023%2F06%2F22%2Fremarks-by-president-biden-and-prime-minister-modi-of-the-republic-of-india-in-joint-press-conference%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EModi%20had%20claimed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20there%20India%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20and%20%E2%80%98DNA%E2%80%99%20ensured%20that%20there%20was%20no%20discrimination%20against%20religious%20minorities%20and%20suppression%20of%20dissent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlso%20speaking%20at%20the%20briefing%2C%20United%20Nations%20Special%20Rapporteur%20of%20Minority%20Rights%20Fernand%20de%20Varennes%20stated%20that%20there%20was%20an%20%E2%80%9Cobvious%20and%20disturbing%20trend%20in%20the%20increasing%20allegations%E2%80%9D%20of%20human%20rights%20violations%20against%20minorities%20in%20India%20that%20are%20being%20submitted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20talking%20of%20millions%20of%20minorities%20who%20are%20directly%20affected%20in%20some%20of%20these%20allegations%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20de%20Varennes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECalling%20on%20US%20to%20put%20pressure%20as%20the%20self-proclaimed%20defender%20of%20global%20human%20rights%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmassive%20persecution%E2%80%9D%20in%20India%20is%20%E2%80%9Cis%20difficult%20to%20reconcile%20with%20democracy%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20we%20are%20now%20seeing%20is%20a%20perversion%20of%20what%20India%20can%20be%2C%20has%20been%2C%20and%20should%20be%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added%2C%20as%20per%20the%20press%20note.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690089528000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F23104709%2FFy52na-X0AY3wnX.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Frashida-tlaib-us-congress-modi-speech-boycott%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'This%20House%20should%20never%20be%20used%20as%20a%20platform%20to%20spread%20bigotry%20and%20hate%2C'%20Tlaib%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A183%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Frashida-tlaib-us-congress-modi-speech-boycott%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Three%20Claims%20of%20Government%20Economists%20About%20Jobs%20Put%20to%20the%20Test%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F23103952%2F3158023774_54f2900169_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EI%20will%20discuss%20three%20claims%20made%20by%20government%20economists%2C%20basing%20my%20analysis%20on%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%20National%20Survey%20Organization%E2%80%99s%20(NSO)%20data%2C%20the%20Labour%20Force%20Surveys.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirst%20claim%3A%20there%20has%20been%20%E2%80%98jobful%20growth%E2%80%99!%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20claimed%20that%20there%20was%20a%2058%20million%20increase%20in%20jobs%20between%20calendar%20years%202019%20and%202022%2C%20the%20highest%20in%20Indian%20history%20over%20three%20years.%20The%20same%20authors%20also%20claim%2C%20bizarrely%2C%20that%20employment%20growth%20from%202004-5%20to%202011-12%20(India%E2%80%99s%20highest%20ever%20GDP%20growth%20period)%20during%20the%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20years%20was%20very%20weak%20%E2%80%93%20just%2013.3%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20claims%20ignore%20that%20most%20of%20the%2058%20million%20%E2%80%98jobs%E2%80%99%20claim%20rests%20upon%20the%20increase%20in%20%E2%80%98employment%E2%80%99%20in%20agriculture%20during%20Covid.%20In%202019%2C%20there%20were%20188%20mn%20workers%20in%20agriculture%3B%20in%20mid-2020%2C%20reverse%20migration%20raised%20it%20by%2045%20million.%20For%20anyone%20believing%20that%20in%202021%2C%20the%20migration%20had%20reversed%20back%20to%20the%20cities%20and%20away%20from%20agriculture%2C%20the%20NSO%20data%20throws%20up%20a%20surprise%3A%20in%202021%2C%207%20mn%20additional%20people%20were%20working%20in%20agriculture%20compared%20to%202020.%20Between%202004-5%20and%202011-12%2C%2037%20million%20workers%20exited%20agriculture%2C%20a%20good%20development%2C%20as%20non-farm%20job%20growth%20rose%20sharply%20to%207.5%20mn%20per%20annum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%C2%A0%20as%20non-farm%20job%20growth%20had%20fallen%20post-2013%20(to%20only%202.9%20mn%20pa%20till%202019)%2C%20the%20rate%20of%20exit%20from%20agriculture%20also%20fell.%20GDP%20growth%20fell%20sharply%20from%202016%20for%20each%20quarter%20until%20Covid%20broke.%20India%E2%80%99s%20open%20unemployment%20rate%20in%202017-18%20had%20risen%20to%20a%2045-year%20high.%20And%20then%20the%20ill-planned%20national%20lockdown%20caused%20massive%20reverse%20migration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgriculture%20is%20labour%20surplus%2C%20and%20rising%20employment%20in%20it%20lowers%20productivity%20and%20real%20incomes%20among%20those%20dependent%20on%20agriculture.%20Worse%2C%20it%20is%20the%20opposite%20of%20the%20structural%20change%20sought%20%E2%80%95%20a%20fall%20in%20the%20share%20of%20agriculture%20in%20GDP%20and%20a%20rise%20in%20non-farm%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorse%20still%2C%20most%20of%20this%20so-called%20increase%20in%20%E2%80%98jobs%E2%80%99%20in%20agriculture%20since%202019%20is%20in%20%E2%80%98unpaid%20family%20labour%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20form%20of%20self-employment%20where%20women%2C%20youth%20and%20children%20join%20other%20family%20members%20to%20appear%20%E2%80%98employed%E2%80%99.%20In%20ILO%E2%80%99s%20definition%2C%20followed%20by%2092%20other%20countries%20but%20not%20India%2C%20for%20no%20reason%20other%20than%20the%20NSO%E2%80%99s%20cussedness%20to%20not%20adopt%20definitions%20that%20ILO%20members%2C%20under%20India%E2%80%99s%20chairmanship%20in%202013%20of%20the%2019%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%C2%A0International%20Conference%20of%20Labour%20Statisticians%2C%20had%20agreed%20upon.%20The%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20the%20Indian%20Economy%2C%20generating%20monthly%20data%20on%20employment%20since%202016%2C%20follows%20the%20ILO%20definition%2C%20and%20hence%20has%20shown%20consistent%20increases%20in%20unemployment%2C%20and%20reductions%20in%20labour%20force%20and%20workforce%20participation%20rates%20in%20India%20since%202016%2C%20while%20NSO%20shows%20the%20opposite%2C%20despite%20falling%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20second%20claim%3A%20real%20wages%20have%20increased%20recently!%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFigure%201%3A%20Real%20Wages%20(in%20Rs.%20at%202011%20price)%20by%20sector%20and%20type%20of%20employment%2C%202018-2022%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPanel%20A%3A%20Agriculture%20%26amp%3B%20Allied%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20cellspacing%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20cellpadding%3D%5C%220%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F0a103129-2325-491e-8a57-536b90df7796%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiYWt5Mm8ifQ.6MWfvlP9rau_ovHEjX2OsfccTssIZEXNjPP_vKEvs5I%