0me.%20After%20the%20film%20ended%2C%20it%20took%20me%20a%20few%20hours%20to%20realise%20that%20it%20reminded%20me%20of%20a%20similar%20piece%20in%20%3Cem%3EStudent%20of%20The%20Year%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2013)%20featuring%20a%20recreated%20version%20of%20Nazia%20Hassan%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EDisco%20Deewane%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Apart%20from%20the%20elegant%20new%20disco%20beats%2C%20it%20occurred%20to%20me%20why%20it%20reminded%20me%20of%20a%20Karan%20Johar%20film%2C%20where%20he%20tried%20to%20conjure%20something%20out%20of%20nothing.%20That%E2%80%99s%20because%20even%20Gerwig%E2%80%99s%20film%20has%20a%20similar%20cloudy%20texture%2C%20where%20everything%20seems%20too%20spruced%20up%20even%20for%20a%20fantasy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20obviously%20not%20a%20bad%20thing.%20There%20are%20enough%20films%20focusing%20on%20materialistic%20excesses%2C%20only%20to%20surprise%20us%20with%20moments%20of%20insight.%20Unfortunately%2C%20%3Cem%3EBarbie%3C%2Fem%3E%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20emerge%20as%20a%20film%20compellingly%20subversive%20or%20original%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20shame%20because%20it%20seems%20sincere%20and%20earnest%20for%20the%20large%20part.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpening%20with%20a%20hilarious%20%3Cem%3E2001%3A%20A%20Space%20Odyssey%3C%2Fem%3E%20gag%2C%20something%20that%20would%20have%20felt%20funnier%20had%20the%20marketing%20executives%20not%20led%20with%20it%20for%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20promotions%2C%20Gerwig%E2%80%99s%20film%20establishes%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20real%20world%20and%20%E2%80%98Barbie%20land%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20an%20alternate%20world%20where%20the%20dolls%20live.%20Barbie%20(Margot%20Robbie)%20%E2%80%93%20we%E2%80%99ll%20later%20find%20out%20that%20she%E2%80%99s%20called%20the%20stereotypical%20Barbie%20%E2%80%93%20wakes%20up%20in%20her%20palatial%20doll%20house.%20She%20wakes%20up%20with%20perfect%20hair%2C%20uses%20a%20slide%20to%20get%20to%20her%20kitchen%2C%20and%20floats%20her%20way%20into%20the%20driver%E2%80%99s%20seat%20of%20a%20car.%20Gerwig%20sets%20the%20rules%20of%20her%20world%20%E2%80%93%20where%20Barbies%20run%20this%20realm%20%E2%80%93%20as%20presidents%2C%20academics%2C%20scientists%20and%20writers.%20The%20men%20in%20this%20world%20%E2%80%93%20called%20Ken%20%E2%80%93%20are%20entrusted%20with%20menial%20work%2C%20like%20standing%20on%20the%20beach%2C%20sporting%20lush%20hair%20and%20perfect%20abs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FpBk4NYhWNMM%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGerwig%E2%80%99s%20film%20focuses%20on%20Robbie%E2%80%99s%20Barbie%20%E2%80%93%20who%20starts%20%E2%80%98malfunctioning%E2%80%99%2C%20after%20she%20wakes%20up%20with%20bad%20breath%2C%20and%20begins%20to%20have%20thoughts%20of%20death.%20We%E2%80%99re%20also%20introduced%20to%20Ken%20(Ryan%20Gosling)%2C%20who%20lives%20only%20to%20get%20Barbie%E2%80%99s%20attention.%20When%20Barbie%20realises%20the%20only%20way%20to%20rectify%20the%20cellulite%20on%20her%20skin%20(and%20the%20%E2%80%98weird%E2%80%99%20thoughts%20she%E2%80%99s%20having)%2C%20is%20to%20go%20to%20the%20real%20world%20and%20meet%20the%20person%20playing%20with%20her%2C%20to%20fix%20the%20%E2%80%98space-time%E2%80%99%20continuum%20between%20Barbie%20Land%20and%20the%20real%20world%2C%20Ken%20accompanies%20her%20%E2%80%93%20an%20act%20of%20reckless%2C%20selfless%20kindness.%20Gosling%2C%20who%20has%20spent%20a%20quarter%20of%20a%20century%20in%20the%20film%20business%20hearing%20about%20his%20%E2%80%98Ken%20doll%E2%80%99%20looks%2C%20is%20disarmingly%20sincere%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20duo%20reach%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20California%2C%20which%20is%20also%20which%20is%20the%20headquarters%20of%20Mattel%2C%20the%20company%20manufacturing%20Barbie%20and%20Ken.%20It%E2%80%99s%20in%20this%20section%20of%20the%20film%20when%20it%20scores%20its%20highest.%20Both%20Barbie%20and%20Ken%20are%20coming%20to%20realise%20that%20the%20real%20world%20might%20be%20just%20a%20%3Cem%3Elittle%3C%2Fem%3E%20different%20from%20what%20they%E2%80%99d%20imagined.%20Gerwig%20keeps%20the%20tone%20light%20even%20as%20both%20Barbie%20and%20Ken%20try%20to%20navigate%20the%20absolute%20opposite%20notions%20of%20the%20genders%20in%20the%20real%20world.%20Over%20here%2C%20men%20run%20things.%20Teenage%20girls%20hate%20dolls%20for%20setting%20unachievable%20standards%20for%20appearances.%20Barbie%20breaks%20down%20on%20learning%20that%20the%20world%20treats%20her%20with%20disrespect%20because%20of%20her%20gender%2C%20while%20Ken%20seems%20to%20be%20enjoying%20all%20the%20new-found%20attention%20he%20gets%20for%20the%20way%20he%20looks%20(and%20also%20his%20gender).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGosling%20is%20a%20hoot%20as%20someone%20who%20can%E2%80%99t%20control%20his%20joy%20after%20%E2%80%98discovering%E2%80%99%20patriarchy%2C%20realising%20the%20real%20world%20values%20him.%20Gosling%20is%20completely%20believable%20as%20he%20sells%20his%20big%2C%20doofus%20smile%20reaching%20the%20conclusion%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20he%20who%20deserves%20to%20be%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20Barbieland%2C%20soon%20to%20be%20renamed%20%E2%80%98Kendom%E2%80%99.%20Robbie%20is%20earnest%20as%20the%20most%20perfect-looking%20person%20to%20have%20ever%20existed%2C%20striving%20to%20be%20more%20than%20her%20looks.%20If%20both%20%3Cem%3EBabylon%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022)%20and%20this%20are%20anything%20to%20go%20by%2C%20nobody%20can%20cry%20better%20than%20her.%20Ironically%2C%20Gerwig%E2%80%99s%20film%20isn%E2%80%99t%20able%20to%20give%20Robbie%20her%20own%20distinct%20flavour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20conceit%20of%20%3Cem%3EBarbie%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20viewing%20the%20age-old%20battle%20of%20sexes%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20the%20equal%20rights%20movement%2C%20is%20an%20interesting%20one.%20It%20succeeds%20to%20an%20extent%2C%20taking%20two%20central%20figures%20who%20defined%20%E2%80%98masculinity%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98femininity%E2%80%99%20for%20an%20entire%20generation%20and%20investigating%20their%20gender%20roles%20in%20a%20Utopian%20setting.%20It%20never%20muddies%20itself%20with%20in-between%20nuances.%20It%E2%80%99s%20either%20war%20between%20Barbies%20and%20Kens%20or%20one%20set%20dominating%20the%20other.%20Gerwig%E2%80%99s%20film%20addresses%20co-existence%2C%20as%20Barbies%20and%20Kens%20discover%20lives%20beyond%20their%20primary%20%E2%80%98functions%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20they%20mostly%20feel%20like%20feeble%20nudges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20disingenuous%20things%20about%20the%20film%20is%20the%20involvement%20of%20Mattel%20%E2%80%93%20which%2C%20while%20at%20one%20level%20can%20be%20perceived%20as%20a%20company%20introspecting%20about%20its%20capitalist%20history%20%E2%80%93%20could%20also%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20company%20trying%20to%20leverage%20its%20%E2%80%9Cself-awareness%E2%80%9D%20for%20image%20purposes.%20Will%20Ferrell%20%E2%80%93%20in%20a%20sensational%20cameo%20%E2%80%93%20plays%20the%20whimsical%2C%20greedy%20CEO%2C%20who%20chases%20Barbie%20and%20Ken%20all%20the%20way%20to%20Barbieland.%20The%20pitch%20of%20%3Cem%3EBarble%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20cartoonishly%20high%2C%20which%20Ferrell%20effortlessly%20matches.%20However%2C%20if%20Greta%20Gerwig%E2%80%99s%20film%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20an%20indictment%20of%20set%20gender%20roles%20and%20men%E2%80%99s%20greed%20fuelling%20those%20notions%2C%20the%20final%20film%20ends%20up%20feeling%20more%20like%20a%20gentle%20reprimand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%2C%20%3Cem%3EBarbie%3C%2Fem%3E%20commits%20the%20cardinal%20sin%3A%20it%20talks%20down%20to%20its%20audience.%20America%20Ferrera%20goes%20on%20a%20feminist%20monologue%20bender%20%E2%80%98turning%E2%80%99%20brainwashed%20and%20servile%20Barbies%20into%20their%20original%20selves.%20It%E2%80